getUtility

public int getUtility(GameState h)
Returns a numeric value for the outcome of the game. In chess, the outcome is a win, loss, or draw, which we can represent by the value +1, -1, or 0. Some games have a wider variety of possible outcomes; for example, the payoffs in backgammon range from + 192 to -192.

Parameters:
h - a game state to evaluate.
Returns:
a numeric value for the outcome of the game.
